Marc's treatment of Kenya is inexcusable, and so is Kenya's treatment of others. Yet, I can't help but wonder about the woman she portrayed herself to be (FYI, not everyone watches this show- my spouse does not unless we happen to be in the same room and I am; even then he can't tell you what's happening - 0 interest)

It's evident Marc does not care for gossip and bickering, and I suspect that it's particularly frustrating when your wife always appears to be the instigator.

His response to Greg and Nene last episode was incredibly mature "I will not split up a couple". This, in response to his wife extending an invitation to Nene's husband and not Nene. How does one crave greater unity within their marriage yet seek to separate a husband from a wife (even if only geographically)? The irony!
It's interesting to me that Kenya's relationship woes have not prompted some introspection on her part.

She claims to champion her husband's endeavours yet she couldn't wait until the event ended to discuss Marlo's reaction. Candy's silence while she spoke was telling - it wasn't the appropriate time to have that conversation.

That image of Marlo and her nephews was incredibly powerful; it embodied her husband's event but she couldn't see that simply because the woman with the two boys was Marlo.
Should Marlo have left? No! But I love that she gave her nephews an explanation for her exit - she told them don't ever let anyone make you feel like you're second. I respect that.

Kenya really had no good reason to seat her at the back. She used her husband's event as an opportunity to exert power over the women.

Every woman deserves a man who can love her completely. I believe Marc has fallen out of love, perhaps he never truly was in love.

As for Kenya, I hope she considers her ways and make some changes because no mature man would tolerate what we see on RHOA. It's unattractive and destructive.
